comment: [Observable in production angle] LATR, an angle not visible to referees on the floor, shows that Crowder (BOS) makes contact with Iguodala's (GSW) arm and Olynyk (BOS) makes contact with Iguodala's head that affects his shot attempt.
Ezeli (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Sullinger's (BOS) drive and shot attempt. Any contact on the play is initiated by Sullinger.
LHH shows that Turner (BOS) trips Curry (GSW). He then grabs his wrist and and pushes him while the two players are on the floor.
Livingston (GSW) sets the screen on Bradley (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Ezeli (GSW) sets the screen on Bradley (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
RATR shows that Bradley (BOS) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
Livingston (GSW) cleanly blocks Thomas' (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Ezeli (GSW) dislodges Crowder (BOS) from behind, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Livingston (GSW) bobbles the ball and does not commit a traveling violation.
Bradley (BOS) does not obtain a legal guarding position and makes contact with Curry's (GSW) body that affects his movement to the basket and shot attempt.
RHH shows that Bogut (GSW) makes contact with Thomas (BOS) that affects his RSBQ on the drive into the paint.
Johnson (BOS) sets the screen on Livingston (GSW) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Johnson (BOS) dislodges Green (GSW) from behind, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Bogut (GSW) cleanly blocks Olynyk's (BOS) layup attempt off the backboard.
Turner (BOS) and Sullinger (BOS) maintain legal guarding position as they trap Curry (GSW) in the corner.
RHH shows that Livingston (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Thomas' (BOS) driving layup attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Iguodala's (GSW) shot attempt at 3:02 of the OT period was a 3 Point Field Goal was upheld.
Olynyk (BOS) makes incidental contact with Curry (GSW) that does not affect his layup attempt.
Iguodala (GSW) firms up as he sets the screen on Turner (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Livingston (GSW) makes incidental contact that does not affect Thomas' (BOS) RSBQ at the start of his drive.
Olynyk (BOS) sets the screen on Barbosa (GSW) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Thomas (BOS) initiates the contact with Barbosa (GSW) who maintains legal guarding position as he defends the drive to the basket.
Thomas (BOS) makes a legal move as he attempts to split the trap.
Iguodala (GSW) makes incidental contact that does not affect Johnson's (BOS) layup attempt.
Curry (GSW) makes incidental contact with Turner (BOS) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Johnson (BOS) sets the screen on Curry (GSW) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bogut (GSW) makes contact with Turner's (BOS) body and head that affects his layup attempt.
Olynyk (BOS) and Green (GSW) legally engage during rebounding.
Curry (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Turner's (BOS) drive to the basket. He trips over his teammate Bogut's (GSW) foot.
Curry (GSW) and Bogut (GSW) maintain legal guarding position as Turner (BOS) drives to the basket and attempts the layup. Bogut blocks the shot prior to any incidental contact with Turner.
Olynyk (BOS) cleanly blocks Barbosa's (GSW) transition layup attempt.
Olynyk (BOS) maintains legal guarding position during Iguodala's (GSW) layup attempt.
Olynyk (BOS) and Barbosa (GSW) make incidental contact with one another as they attempt to establish post position.
Curry (GSW) steps OOB while in possession of the ball.
Young (BOS) is retreating and maintains legal guarding position as he contests Curry's (GSW) transition shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Thomas (BOS) was upheld. Golden State retained possession.
RHH shows that Livingston (GSW) and Curry (GSW) maintain legal guarding position as they trap Sullinger (BOS) on the baseline.
Correctly called 24 Second Violation.
Johnson (BOS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Green's (GSW) driving layup attempt.
Iguodala (GSW) makes incidental contact with Turner (BOS) that does not affect his movement to the basket and layup attempt.
L-SLASH shows that Thomas (BOS) makes contact with Livingston (GSW) that affects his RSBQ.
Jerebko (BOS) and Crowder (BOS) maintain legal guarding position as they contest Ezeli's (GSW) shot attempt.

Crowder (BOS) does not obtain a legal guarding position and pulls Livingston (GSW) into him causing both players to go to the floor. LATR and LHH show that the illegal contact occurs prior to Livingston stepping OOB.
RHH shows that Livingston (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Crowder's (BOS) drive to the basket and layup attempt. Any contact on the play is initiated by Crowder.
Thomas (BOS) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Curry (GSW) legally contests Crowder's (BOS) jump shot attempt. Any contact on the play is created by Crowder who extends his leg on the shot attempt.
Sullinger (BOS) commits a take foul on Iguodala (GSW).
